2. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION ANALYSIS
================================================================================

2.1 Amazon Cognito User Pools
   Location: amplify/backend/auth/petstoresample483a619c/
   User Pool ID: sa-east-1_LAeXR4OOV
   App Client ID: [COGNITO_CLIENT_ID_REDACTED]
   
   Configuration:
   - Identity Pool: petstoresample483a619c_identitypool_483a619c
   - MFA: OFF
   - Auto-verified attributes: email
   - Required attributes: email
   - Password policy: Minimum 8 characters
   - Token validity: 30 days refresh token
   
   User Groups:
   - Customer: Basic customer access
   - StoreOwnerRole: Store management access
   - FranchiseOwnerRole: Franchise management access
   
   Custom Attributes (from authorizer code):
   - custom:franchiseCode: Comma-separated franchise IDs
   - custom:employmentStoreCode: Comma-separated store IDs
   
   Token Type: ID Token (tokenUse: "id")
   Format: JWT Bearer token in Authorization header

2.2 AWS Verified Permissions (AVP)
   Location: amplify/backend/custom/petstoreAVPPolicyStore/
   Policy Language: Cedar
   
   Entity Types (from policySchema.json):
   - MyApplication::User
   - MyApplication::Group
   - MyApplication::Store
   - MyApplication::StoreFranchise
   - MyApplication::Pet
   - MyApplication::Order
   - MyApplication::Application
   
   Actions Defined:
   - SearchPets: Browse pet catalog
   - AddPet: Create new pet record
   - UpdatePet: Modify pet information
   - DeletePet: Remove pet (not used)
   - PlaceOrder: Create new order
   - GetOrder: View order details
   - CancelOrder: Cancel existing order
   - ListOrders: View all orders for a store
   - GetStoreInventory: View inventory levels
   
   Sample Policies (from policySamples.json):
   
   CustomerPolicy1:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"Customer",
       action in [SearchPets, PlaceOrder],
       resource
     );
   
   CustomerPolicy2:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"Customer",
       action in [GetOrder],
       resource
     ) when {
       principal == resource.owner
     };
   
   FranchiseOwnerPolicy1:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"FranchiseOwnerRole",
       action in [GetStoreInventory, ListOrders],
       resource
     ) when {
       principal has employmentStoreFranchiseCodes &&
       resource in (principal.employmentStoreFranchiseCodes)
     };
   
   FranchiseOwnerPolicy2:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"FranchiseOwnerRole",
       action in [GetOrder],
       resource
     ) when {
       principal has employmentStoreFranchiseCodes &&
       resource.store in (principal.employmentStoreFranchiseCodes)
     };
   
   StoreOwnerPolicy1:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"StoreOwnerRole",
       action in [GetStoreInventory, ListOrders],
       resource
     ) when {
       resource in (principal.employmentStoreCodes)
     };
   
   StoreOwnerPolicy2:
     permit (
       principal in MyApplication::Group::"StoreOwnerRole",
       action in [GetOrder],
       resource
     ) when {
       resource.store in (principal.employmentStoreCodes)
     };

